The paper deals with distributed estimation in wireless sensor networks, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The use of quantization and modulation techniques suggests a focus on signal processing (cs.SY) and multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the optimization of power and bandwidth allocation involves mathematical optimization (cs.MA).
